WEBVTT

00:00.226 --> 00:06.995
As we move from gathering to listening, our scripture reading today is from the book of Mark, chapter 10, verses 35 to 45.

00:08.858 --> 00:12.403
Then James and John, the sons of Zebedee, came to him.

00:13.184 --> 00:16.528
Teacher, they said, we want you to do for us whatever we ask.

00:17.930 --> 00:19.112
What do you want me to do for you?

00:19.172 --> 00:19.592
He asked.

00:20.514 --> 00:25.881
They replied, but one of us sit at your right and the other sit at your left in your glory.

00:27.363 --> 00:29.586
You don't know what you're asking, Jesus said.

00:30.210 --> 00:35.235
Can you drink the cup I drink or be baptized with the baptism I am baptized with?

00:36.817 --> 00:37.838
We can, they answered.

00:38.999 --> 00:45.006
Jesus said to them, you will drink the cup I drink and be baptized with the baptism I am baptized with.

00:45.687 --> 00:48.910
But to sit at my right or left is not for me to grant.

00:49.671 --> 00:52.274
These places belong to those for whom they have been prepared.

00:53.695 --> 00:57.139
When the 10 heard about this, they became indignant with James and John.

00:58.140 --> 00:59.922
Jesus called them together and said,

01:00.610 --> 01:08.763
You know that those who are regarded as the rulers of the Gentiles lorded over them, and their high officials exercise authority over them.

01:09.664 --> 01:10.406
Not so with you.

01:10.426 --> 01:19.821
Instead, whoever wants to become great among you must be your servant, and whoever wants to be first must be slave of all.

01:20.962 --> 01:28.274
For even the Son of Man did not come to be served, but to serve, and to give his life as a ransom for many.

01:29.474 --> 01:30.553
This is the word of the Lord.

01:31.448 --> 01:32.018
Thanks be to God.

01:39.138 --> 01:43.763
Well, this morning we are thrilled that Donna Barber is here with us this morning.

01:43.803 --> 01:47.868
For many of you, you know Donna, she is a longtime friend of Antioch.

01:47.888 --> 01:57.919
She lives in Portland now, native to Philadelphia, but Donna has worked tirelessly to advance the causes of justice, both in the church and outside the church, particularly in the areas of education reform.

01:58.439 --> 02:08.370
Currently she serves as the executive director of the Voices Project, which is a ministry we support here at Antioch, but it works to help minority voices

02:08.546 --> 02:12.391
They're minority folks develop their voices and step into leadership role.

02:12.411 --> 02:14.293
So let's give Donna and warm Antioch welcome.

02:22.684 --> 02:23.885
Good morning, Antioch.

02:25.467 --> 02:27.830
It is good to be with you again.

02:27.870 --> 02:30.113
We praise God for his grace.

02:30.854 --> 02:31.555
Thank you, Lord.

02:32.736 --> 02:34.098
For all of you that

02:34.434 --> 02:50.073
made your way here today, the things that you pushed through, the things you went around and under and over, the things you decided to let go, the way you chose to trust the voice of God that was leading you here this morning.

02:50.093 --> 02:55.060
I wanna thank you for that and thank God for his faithfulness.

02:56.141 --> 02:56.622
Let's pray.

02:58.624 --> 03:03.410
Lord, we do bless and thank you and glorify your name today.

03:04.322 --> 03:06.685
Thank you, God, that you were here before we got here.

03:07.365 --> 03:09.828
Thank you, Lord, for the angels that are ministering.

03:09.948 --> 03:19.598
Thank you, God, for each soul that is in the building and those that are desirous of being here, but for whatever reasons cannot.

03:20.599 --> 03:22.461
Lord, we pray that you meet us today.

03:23.723 --> 03:30.770
Lord, God, that you place in our minds, in our hearts, in our spirits, your intentions,

03:31.202 --> 03:34.826
Give us your understanding of your word, Lord God.

03:34.886 --> 03:40.592
Give us personal and corporate application in the name of Jesus.

03:40.993 --> 03:45.397
And for this, Lord, we say thank you and give you all glory in Jesus' name.

03:45.978 --> 03:46.318
Amen.

03:50.603 --> 04:00.754
So this morning, we are looking at the words from the gospel according to Brother Mark.

04:02.498 --> 04:14.112
And in the first chapters of that book, Mark outlines a series of events about the ministry of Jesus.

04:15.174 --> 04:23.604
And as you walk through that book, he tells us about Jesus calling the disciples and casting out of demons.

04:23.704 --> 04:28.210
He talks about various healings and parables.

04:28.386 --> 04:32.831
about wine and wineskins, about sewers and soils.

04:33.432 --> 04:36.675
He talks about lamps and mustard seeds.

04:37.156 --> 04:38.617
There are miracles.

04:39.018 --> 04:41.260
There are feeding of thousands.

04:41.861 --> 04:45.325
There is even Jesus walking on water.

04:46.126 --> 04:49.910
There is the mountaintop transfiguration.

04:51.912 --> 04:57.458
And through all of this now, the disciples are walking with him.

04:57.730 --> 05:04.079
They are moving with him from town to town, from place to place.

05:04.479 --> 05:05.781
They are observers.

05:05.881 --> 05:20.161
They are participants as they move through Capernaum and Galilee and the country of the Gatorines and the coast of Decapolis and into the parts of Dalmanutha.

05:20.181 --> 05:22.805
They are listening to his message.

05:23.205 --> 05:26.610
They are seeing the miraculous

05:26.978 --> 05:28.019
in their presence.

05:29.521 --> 05:39.634
And after all of that, we get to chapter nine, and the disciples are whispering among themselves an animated conversation.

05:42.478 --> 05:49.667
And Jesus asks a question, as Jesus likes to do, of course, that he already knows the answer to.

05:51.529 --> 05:55.154
So what is it you're talking about, boys?

05:58.050 --> 06:00.614
What is that you were disputing about among yourselves?

06:02.898 --> 06:08.066
And Jesus is met with silence the way our kids are sometimes.

06:08.086 --> 06:09.388
What are you all doing?

06:11.952 --> 06:12.212
Right?

06:13.154 --> 06:23.410
This is how the disciples respond to Jesus because they have been talking about who among them should be the greatest.

06:25.186 --> 06:38.643
So Jesus and his patience and his grace and his love calls them together and says, you know, if you desire to be first, then you'll need to be last.

06:40.125 --> 06:42.348
You'll need to be servant of all.

06:44.230 --> 06:45.632
Okay, we got that fellas.

06:46.213 --> 06:47.695
He has that little talk with them, right?

06:48.095 --> 06:53.522
So they go on and they keep traveling and Jesus keeps teaching.

06:54.242 --> 06:58.286
They continue walking, and Jesus blesses some children.

06:58.306 --> 07:05.212
He talks to them and others about the challenges of wealth.

07:06.273 --> 07:15.202
He talks about the rewards of faithfulness, and he foretells his impending death and resurrection.

07:17.444 --> 07:23.570
And after all of that, after all of these miraculous conversations,

07:23.842 --> 07:26.225
these deep, meaningful teachings.

07:27.948 --> 07:35.178
James and John, bless them, come to Jesus with a request.

07:38.122 --> 07:41.848
Teacher, we want you to do something for us.

07:45.052 --> 07:51.762
And Jesus asks, again, knowing, what is it you want me to do for you?

07:53.986 --> 07:56.730
What is it you want me to do for you?

07:59.233 --> 08:02.317
Do you ever hear the Lord asking you that question?

08:03.799 --> 08:15.295
Sometimes in the middle of the praying and the asking and the crying and all of the things, what is it you want me to do for you?

08:18.939 --> 08:20.882
James and John's responses,

08:22.082 --> 08:25.986
Allow us to sit on your right and your left hand in your kingdom.

08:26.607 --> 08:29.530
We wanna be your right hand and your left hand, man.

08:29.610 --> 08:31.392
We wanna be your number twos.

08:31.913 --> 08:33.494
We can help run this thing, Jesus.

08:35.557 --> 08:38.820
Now for days, they have been watching.

08:39.461 --> 08:40.782
They have been listening.

08:41.403 --> 08:42.865
They have been following.

08:43.826 --> 08:45.227
And this is where they land.

08:49.792 --> 08:51.474
Because they've been seeing power.

08:52.642 --> 08:54.244
They've been seeing popularity.

08:55.165 --> 08:57.949
They have interpreted things as fame.

08:58.009 --> 09:01.754
They have been watching the crowds grow.

09:01.775 --> 09:10.246
They've also, it seems, been sizing up the other disciples, looking at them and looking at themselves.

09:10.727 --> 09:15.033
And they have concluded that they are the best men for the job.

09:18.738 --> 09:21.842
And they've decided to take initiative and step up

09:23.778 --> 09:28.745
And they asked Jesus, make us number two, we got this.

09:31.028 --> 09:34.914
And Jesus says, you don't know what you're asking.

09:38.940 --> 09:43.867
I think he says that to us sometimes too, because we don't know.

09:43.887 --> 09:51.858
Whenever we come with a request beyond your will be done,

09:53.506 --> 09:55.648
We do not know what we are asking.

10:01.654 --> 10:09.121
He says, if you abide in me and I in you, you can ask what you will, but even then we don't know.

10:09.181 --> 10:19.370
Jesus taught us to pray, give us this day our daily bread, lead us not into temptation, deliver us from evil.

10:19.751 --> 10:23.474
It's not the only prayer, but it's the best.

10:25.826 --> 10:31.836
But we tend to come with our laundry list of requests because we think we know.

10:33.238 --> 10:36.303
We think we know what we want.

10:37.625 --> 10:40.409
We think we know what we need.

10:41.832 --> 10:45.237
We think we know how things should go.

10:45.698 --> 10:50.446
We think we know right from wrong and good, from evil.

10:50.746 --> 10:53.170
We think we thought it through

10:53.250 --> 10:58.378
We can handle it, we can manage what it is we are asking for.

10:58.818 --> 11:00.321
We've got this, God.

11:00.822 --> 11:03.065
I need you to do some things for me.

11:07.812 --> 11:11.498
And Jesus responds, are you able?

11:14.222 --> 11:19.550
Are you able to handle this thing you are asking for of me?

11:20.872 --> 11:22.194
Are you able to drink

11:22.498 --> 11:30.629
from the cup I drink from, he asked James and John, are you able to be baptized with the baptism that I'm baptized with?

11:31.030 --> 11:33.233
Are you able, James and John?

11:36.377 --> 11:47.092
And James and John doubled down in pride, in arrogance, maybe in ignorance or in innocence.

11:47.172 --> 11:51.218
They really think they can and they say, yes, we can.

11:53.634 --> 11:59.781
It would seem when Jesus asked them that question, right, coming back, are you able to drink?

11:59.801 --> 12:02.864
You're gonna drink from the cup, you're gonna be baptized with the baptism.

12:03.345 --> 12:07.769
There's something in them should've said, hmm.

12:07.789 --> 12:08.670
You know what, Jesus?

12:09.331 --> 12:09.972
We're sorry.

12:10.232 --> 12:12.294
You know, just going back to what you were doing.

12:12.675 --> 12:14.036
We're just gonna step away.

12:14.317 --> 12:23.026
You would think that something would occlude them in like, no, but no, because we think we know.

12:25.890 --> 12:29.376
Jesus tells us it's hard.

12:30.037 --> 12:31.499
That riches are a hard thing.

12:32.721 --> 12:35.385
Wealth is a hard thing for man to manage.

12:36.307 --> 12:41.435
He tells us that it's hard for a rich man to enter the kingdom.

12:41.515 --> 12:45.081
It's harder than a camel going through the eye of a needle.

12:45.321 --> 12:53.074
He teaches that straight up and we respond, try me.

12:54.402 --> 12:55.944
I can handle the riches.

12:56.865 --> 12:57.706
Give them to me.

12:58.186 --> 12:59.367
It won't be me.

12:59.387 --> 13:00.228
God, I got it.

13:01.069 --> 13:02.411
I can do this thing.

13:03.552 --> 13:04.793
I'm the exception.

13:06.775 --> 13:07.516
That's what we think.

13:09.498 --> 13:10.379
Lottery dreams.

13:10.419 --> 13:10.880
You know what?

13:10.900 --> 13:12.722
If I just win, you know what?

13:12.742 --> 13:14.143
God, I will be able to handle it.

13:15.164 --> 13:17.847
Really, I'm going to give a tithe to the church.

13:17.907 --> 13:19.849
I'm going to give some stuff to missions.

13:20.290 --> 13:21.571
I'm going to help my family.

13:22.012 --> 13:24.274
God, you can trust me with the millions.

13:26.402 --> 13:45.949
Despite the fact that we know that it has been reported that many times the lives of lottery winners end in tragedy, it has been reported that they are bombarded with the constant barrage of people asking for money.

13:46.850 --> 13:52.298
That 70% of lottery winners go bankrupt within a few years.

13:53.239 --> 13:55.122
That people commit suicide.

13:56.130 --> 14:04.378
that their relationships with friends and family members are strained and many couples end up in divorce.

14:05.899 --> 14:11.725
That if they are single, they have a harder time finding life partners after they win.

14:13.126 --> 14:17.831
There have even been some who have been robbed and killed for their winnings.

14:21.074 --> 14:25.298
But still, right now, someone is saying, but I could

14:27.362 --> 14:30.185
Right now, somebody in here, I could do it though.

14:37.193 --> 14:41.638
Somebody's asking, why hasn't God sent me that spouse I've been praying for?

14:42.659 --> 14:45.482
Why hasn't God given me that job that I wanted?

14:46.884 --> 14:50.528
Why hasn't he answered the prayer I have been praying?

14:53.611 --> 14:56.114
God in his love and in his grace,

14:56.898 --> 14:59.481
says, daughter, do you know what you're asking for?

15:01.964 --> 15:04.727
Can you handle all that will come with that thing?

15:07.390 --> 15:10.673
But we, like James and John, often say, yes.

15:11.374 --> 15:12.636
Yes, I can.

15:12.656 --> 15:18.302
But we don't know what we don't know.

15:20.925 --> 15:25.490
And furthermore, we are asking for those things because sometimes

15:26.370 --> 15:38.929
We like them have totally missed what God has spent days and weeks and months and years trying to teach us.

15:42.735 --> 15:47.342
James and John says, yes, we are able, put us in charge.

15:50.868 --> 15:54.994
Sometimes, sometimes God gives us exactly what we ask for.

15:57.026 --> 16:02.092
Jesus responded, you shall indeed drink of that cup that I drink.

16:02.112 --> 16:05.296
You shall indeed be baptized with the baptism.

16:05.737 --> 16:12.025
You think power, fame, and glory, but there is suffering and death that comes with this thing.

16:13.967 --> 16:26.162
We read in Acts 12 to later that Herod, desiring to increase his popularity with the Jews, kills James.

16:26.370 --> 16:27.051
with the sword.

16:30.114 --> 16:42.026
John suffered the loss of his brother and many of his friends and spent years in forced exile on the island of Patmos.

16:42.046 --> 16:46.711
He escaped many near-death experiences on several occasions.

16:48.032 --> 16:53.938
He said, you shall drink of this cup and be baptized with this baptism.

16:55.746 --> 16:57.828
The right and the left is not mine to give.

17:00.531 --> 17:05.056
Now, the other disciples have overheard this conversation.

17:05.076 --> 17:09.361
And they're on the sidelines becoming a little indignant.

17:11.924 --> 17:19.572
You know, I imagine, especially like Peter, right, talking to Andrew, who do they think they are?

17:19.893 --> 17:23.356
If anybody gonna be the leader, it's gonna be me, right?

17:23.376 --> 17:24.818
And they're having their little

17:25.026 --> 17:28.491
thing about it too, because they feel in some kind of way, right?

17:32.157 --> 17:36.042
I imagine Jesus, like, is anyone been listening to me?

17:36.483 --> 17:44.194
I've been talking, I've been teaching, is anyone of these jokers been listening?

17:44.214 --> 17:49.362
Because later he says, have I been so long with you and you still don't know me?

17:52.738 --> 17:53.860
John later went right.

17:53.960 --> 18:00.711
He was in the world and the world was made by him and the world knew him not.

18:04.497 --> 18:06.240
Jesus again calls them together.

18:06.280 --> 18:08.243
Get over here.

18:08.904 --> 18:10.707
Well, no, that's what I would say.

18:10.727 --> 18:14.152
It's not probably not the way Jesus said it.

18:15.455 --> 18:16.957
He's nice and gracious.

18:18.800 --> 18:20.082
Verse 42,

18:20.226 --> 18:23.610
He brings them together again and they got to have another little talk.

18:25.231 --> 18:28.935
And he says, they have ruled the Gentiles, lorded over them.

18:28.975 --> 18:31.798
They terrorize them.

18:31.858 --> 18:36.163
We love power.

18:38.686 --> 18:44.932
Because we have this perception of privilege and control that goes with it.

18:46.274 --> 18:50.098
You can even see it in children playing, right?

18:50.914 --> 18:53.057
fighting over who's in charge of the game.

18:54.239 --> 18:59.267
They're playing make believe, I'm gonna be the dad, I'm gonna be the teacher, I'm gonna be the boss.

18:59.347 --> 19:02.091
No, you're the students.

19:02.131 --> 19:04.836
They even argue with that.

19:05.196 --> 19:09.182
Already, something has told them it's better to be the one in charge.

19:09.683 --> 19:11.146
I wonder where they're, get that from.

19:12.087 --> 19:16.594
And then in our workplaces, on the sports field.

19:20.898 --> 19:25.082
in our churches, in our government.

19:28.907 --> 19:35.474
This leadership is not seen as seats of service, but of power.

19:39.678 --> 19:43.022
When the music plays, all of you are going to bow down to me.

19:44.143 --> 19:47.186
When I walk by, everybody bows down.

19:51.426 --> 20:03.904
Europe in their poor underclass, who have been trapped in subservient roles, came to a new world.

20:07.028 --> 20:17.062
And while talking and writing about democracy and equality, instead, they claimed power.

20:18.064 --> 20:19.826
And they enslaved millions.

20:20.258 --> 20:36.874
and they created a new world underclass made up of women and immigrants and refugees because the people who were on the bottom on one continent decided we're going to be on top in this one.

20:38.295 --> 20:50.066
And today, still an underclass of black and brown, of poor and working poor,

20:50.882 --> 20:56.969
of the imprisoned and the formerly incarcerated, of the immigrant and the refugee.

20:59.272 --> 21:09.123
Because we can only feel good about having more, about being above if we have someone who has less and who is beneath us.

21:13.588 --> 21:18.674
But Jesus says to his disciples, then and now,

21:19.394 --> 21:22.659
It shall not be so among you.

21:25.183 --> 21:30.851
Whosoever will be great will be your minister, your servant.

21:32.294 --> 21:40.887
Whosoever desires to be first, to be chief, to be top needs to be servant of everybody.

21:43.811 --> 21:44.973
See, we don't like servant.

21:47.256 --> 21:48.498
We have a Hollywood

21:48.994 --> 21:51.177
picture in our minds of what that means.

21:51.517 --> 21:53.580
We have a devil wears product.

21:55.362 --> 21:56.564
And we don't want to be Emily.

21:58.967 --> 22:07.058
We don't want to be the doormat, the oneness abused, or the nothing, the one that is just a means to a cheap prosperity.

22:07.439 --> 22:09.261
We don't want to be the servant.

22:09.341 --> 22:12.085
We want to be the devil.

22:16.210 --> 22:18.994
Jesus says, you don't know.

22:19.266 --> 22:20.247
who I am.

22:20.307 --> 22:32.721
The son did not come to be served, but to serve and to give his life a ransom for many.

22:36.945 --> 22:41.991
The night before Jesus was betrayed, Jesus attempts to wash Peter's feet.

22:42.571 --> 22:43.873
And Peter's like, no.

22:46.155 --> 22:48.658
Jesus, you don't know how this king thing works.

22:48.738 --> 22:50.320
You're not supposed to be washing feet.

22:52.163 --> 22:55.969
And Jesus says, Peter, if I don't wash your feet, you got no part with me.

22:58.292 --> 23:00.856
Over and over and over again.

23:01.897 --> 23:08.427
He is teaching us, training us, telling us what it's like to be part of his kingdom.

23:10.270 --> 23:16.018
And that in the kingdom of God, we serve.

23:16.038 --> 23:18.642
And the greatest in the kingdom.

23:19.394 --> 23:20.295
serves all.

23:22.958 --> 23:26.883
Why did James and John ask for this?

23:29.286 --> 23:32.229
And why were the disciples grumbling about it?

23:36.094 --> 23:37.615
Because they were missing it.

23:39.938 --> 23:42.581
Jesus was right there.

23:43.943 --> 23:46.706
The Word of God incarnate.

23:47.362 --> 23:54.632
the creator of all things, the life and light of the world.

23:55.914 --> 24:02.362
He was right there living with them, talking with them.

24:06.248 --> 24:09.692
The prophets of old, they desire to see God.

24:09.993 --> 24:11.595
Lord, show me your glory.

24:11.895 --> 24:13.778
And you can't look at me and live.

24:15.618 --> 24:23.951
So God placed himself in a body and came and lived and walked among them right there.

24:26.896 --> 24:29.180
But they were listening to his message and couldn't hear.

24:30.783 --> 24:42.802
They were following literally in his footsteps and had no idea of what he was doing, who he was, or even who they were.

24:45.410 --> 24:54.643
They came to Jesus saying, Rabbi, teacher, because they saw him as a man.

24:56.666 --> 25:01.793
They thought he was organizing a coup to overthrow the Roman government.

25:02.094 --> 25:06.680
And they wanted to secure seats of power in the new administration.

25:09.304 --> 25:13.330
And the omniscient Christ looks right through them.

25:15.266 --> 25:37.490
look like he looks through our righteous disguises, through our prayers, and he sees our hearts, and he sees their desire to be served, their thoughts of next time we're going to be on top.

25:41.250 --> 25:46.318
Because when you've been living in an oppressed state, sometimes you take on the ways of the oppressor.

25:49.643 --> 25:54.490
Our desire to be great often leads to injustice.

25:57.514 --> 26:02.121
Jesus said, it shall not be named so among you.

26:04.185 --> 26:06.869
It is different in my kingdom.

26:06.929 --> 26:10.514
We don't lord over each other.

26:10.914 --> 26:14.419
We don't exercise authority upon others.

26:15.501 --> 26:18.084
We don't have to do that to be important.

26:21.109 --> 26:30.322
We are His workmanship created in Christ Jesus to do good, to do justice.

26:33.250 --> 26:45.051
The many times like the disciples, we are trying to negotiate something in the kingdom through earthly means with natural understanding.

26:45.111 --> 26:51.442
And Jesus is saying again and again, my kingdom is not of this world.

26:54.754 --> 27:04.363
We are called to transcend our humanity, to live in a divine kingdom, to look beyond earthly power structures.

27:05.465 --> 27:12.131
Jesus speaks to their spirit, through the spirit, and says greatness comes through serving.

27:12.852 --> 27:15.574
Life gained comes through life lost.

27:16.075 --> 27:20.099
Power doesn't come through pursuit, but through surrender.

27:22.241 --> 27:23.282
They've been walking.

27:23.586 --> 27:27.311
from city to city, day after day.

27:27.871 --> 27:32.417
Jesus has been talking about the kingdom of heaven.

27:32.858 --> 27:37.283
They have been thinking about an earthly kingdom.

27:40.167 --> 27:45.834
Jesus has been revealing himself as the son of God.

27:48.398 --> 27:51.922
They have been engaging with him as rabbi.

27:52.866 --> 27:54.609
and it would be earthly king.

27:58.134 --> 27:59.796
How are you approaching Jesus?

28:03.622 --> 28:07.287
How are you thinking about this kingdom of God?

28:11.173 --> 28:13.176
How are you thinking about yourself?

28:16.000 --> 28:19.826
About power, about authority,

28:21.122 --> 28:33.362
about your place in the world, what it means to be first, what it means to be leader, what it means to be a child of the Most High God.

28:36.767 --> 28:40.093
What do our prayers suggest we believe?

28:41.796 --> 28:44.400
What do our worries tell us?

28:45.562 --> 28:48.146
What do our fears convey?

28:51.554 --> 28:52.696
And what are our hopes?

28:56.821 --> 29:08.297
James and John came to the Word, to the Son of God, to the Creator of the ends of the earth with a question.

29:08.738 --> 29:12.743
And Jesus asked them, what do you want me to do for you?

29:15.888 --> 29:17.490
And they responded,

29:17.602 --> 29:22.047
We want to be vice president and chief of staff in your administration.

29:26.253 --> 29:29.056
They didn't recognize who they were talking to.

29:33.321 --> 29:38.628
How many times are we approaching God and we don't know who we're talking to?

29:41.291 --> 29:43.594
Things that we're worrying about talking about.

29:44.134 --> 29:47.058
We don't know who we're talking to.

29:52.066 --> 29:57.032
Jesus had a conversation with a woman at the well, asked her for a drink of water.

29:59.055 --> 30:05.423
And she responds, how is it that you being a Jew asked me for a drink of water?

30:09.388 --> 30:17.298
Jesus said, if you knew who it was that was asking, you'd be asking me for water.

30:20.258 --> 30:22.441
so many times he was right there.

30:24.784 --> 30:26.066
And they didn't see him.

30:28.029 --> 30:29.931
He is right here.

30:30.953 --> 30:35.519
He is showing up for us day after day after day.

30:35.559 --> 30:37.722
And we miss him.

30:39.043 --> 30:43.710
We are worrying about things that we don't have to worry about.

30:46.153 --> 30:49.778
We are children of the most high God.

30:55.010 --> 30:59.956
He was found in the likeness of men, but he is not just a man.

31:01.878 --> 31:05.602
Jesus would later ask, whom do men say that I am?

31:07.745 --> 31:12.530
And then Peter would respond, thou art the Christ, the son of the living God.

31:13.151 --> 31:14.953
He's like, ha, there you go, Peter.

31:17.856 --> 31:23.122
Flesh and blood has not revealed that to you, but my father in heaven.

31:24.738 --> 31:28.645
When we recognize who he is, we understand.

31:28.685 --> 31:30.347
We are important.

31:31.229 --> 31:38.180
Not because of titles or positions or possessions, but because we are loved by God.

31:40.685 --> 31:41.626
You don't have to worry.

31:41.646 --> 31:45.893
We don't have to have earthly power to be great.

31:47.476 --> 31:51.122
Dr. King said everyone can be great because everyone can serve.

31:52.418 --> 31:59.209
We can do random acts of kindness, not to get noticed, but because it's the right thing to do.

31:59.269 --> 32:08.164
The kind thing to do, the loving thing to do, the least I can do in light of all that God has done for me.

32:09.646 --> 32:10.127
Jesus.

32:12.671 --> 32:15.415
He says, some of us, we've been hanging out with him for a long time.

32:16.257 --> 32:17.719
We've been following him around.

32:17.739 --> 32:19.602
We've been listening to his words.

32:21.730 --> 32:24.614
and he is asking us, what do you want me to do for you?

32:28.138 --> 32:34.126
How we answer has a lot to do with our understanding of who he is and the kingdom.

32:36.149 --> 32:37.991
Jesus taught his disciples to pray.

32:40.394 --> 32:49.426
He said, our Father, who art in heaven, hallowed as your name, your kingdom come, your will be done.

32:50.434 --> 32:52.179
on earth as it is in heaven.

32:54.767 --> 32:59.982
It's not the only prayer we can pray, but it's the best.

33:02.248 --> 33:02.529
Amen.

33:03.933 --> 33:04.274
Amen.

